    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-14T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-14T20:00:00-05:00" n="184"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/3149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-14T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >August 14, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 15—4:07 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1050. Yesterday Military and Naval Attachés had conversation with newly appointed
                    Minister of War<note n="28" xml:id="d184fn28">José Joaquín Castro
                        Martínez.</note> at latter’s request during which the Minister made
                    following requests: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>That we establish hydroplane service between Cartagena and San Andrés
                            to provide at least one round trip a week for the purpose <pb
                                facs="0174" n="160" xml:id="pg_160"/> of furnishing certain vital
                            items of food and medical supplies required by Colombian army troops and
                            civilian population there.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>That we furnish aerial transportation for Colombian officer to San
                            Andrés and return to mainland for the purpose of surveying present
                            situation and needs of Archipelago.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>That at least part of Colombia’s order for six Catalina flying boats
                            be filled at once.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>When it was pointed out to the Minister that such a service would necessitate
                    arrangements at Cartagena for refueling and maintenance of aircraft employed in
                    this service the Minister stated that he would wish us to take advantage of this
                    situation to patrol coast line of Colombia and thus make airplane serve double
                    purpose to mutual interest of our two countries.</p>
                <p>I recommend that no action be taken on these requests pending approval of our
                    request mentioned in my telegram No. 1049, August 14, 7 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
